The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Anil stake in media outfit

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, May 14: Reliance Capital of the Anil Dhirubhai Ambani Group (ADAG) has acquired a 5 per cent stake in media holding company, Network 18 Fincap Ltd.

 Last month, Reliance Capital made an open offer for an additional 20 per cent stake in TV Today Network. Reliance Capital today informed the stock exchanges that it has acquired 2,555,003 shares of Network 18 Fincap. 

 This translates into an equity holding of 5.02 per cent in the company. The shares were acquired from the open market on May 10. Network 18 Fincap Ltd, registered as an NBFC with the Reserve Bank of India, makes strategic and financial investments. The company operates channels such as CNBC-TV18 and CNBC-Awaaz in India. 

 The NBFC holds about 49.18 per cent stake in Television Eighteen India Ltd and 38.95 per cent in Global Broadcast News Ltd. Reliance Capital holds about 6.27 per cent in Global Broadcast News Ltd. (GBN), which operates the news channel CNN-IBN and Hindi channel IBN.In April, Reliance Capital Ltd made the open offer for an additional 20 per cent in TVToday Network.

 The company expects to spend Rs 151 crore to mop up the shares. Reliance Capital made the offer because its stake in TV Today Network has crossed 15 per cent. The offer for up to1.16 crore shares at Rs 130.50 per share is not subject to a minimum level of acceptance and will be open from June 6 to June 25.TV Today runs the Hindi news channel Aaj Tak and the English channel, Headlines Today. It also has two more Hindi channels in its fold Tez and Dilli Aaj Tak. Almost two years ago, Reliance Capital acquired a significant stake in Adlabs Films. 




